OriginalText.Phrase: SVmme laudis o maria fac vt
Quid non putas male sanus liuor furens liuidus
Sed quis contra nos se credat
Sed quis contra nos se credat

Note.EditorialCommentary: The melodic pattern of the Bassus at this point, imitated a breve later by the Tenor and combined with a staggered cadential formula in the upper two voices (mm. 212-14), draws directly upon the style of writing typical in double-canons at the upper fourth such as Salve radix from LonBLR 11 E.xi.
